parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shattering of the sunroof can cause injury to occupants from flying glass and potentially lead to accidents due to driver distraction.
symptoms: Sunroof explodes or shatters without any apparent external cause
glass fragments everywhere
no evidence of external impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sharp trim on the center console can cause lacerations or cuts to occupants, especially when reaching for items or cleaning the interior.
symptoms: Trim on center console above shifter and below center cubby is razor-sharp
has caused cuts or lacerations to occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leaks through the panoramic sunroof can cause electrical short circuits, potentially leading to fires, and may also cause water damage to the interior and electrical systems.
symptoms: Water leaks through the panoramic sunroof
especially on the driver's side and passenger side front area near the A-pillar and sunvisor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty shift lever micro switch can cause the vehicle to roll away, potentially leading to accidents or injuries, as the key can be removed from the ignition switch without the shift lever being in the "P" park position.
symptoms: Key can be removed from the ignition switch without the shift lever being in the "P" park position
vehicle may roll away
noncompliance with 49 CFR 571.114 standard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Suction Jet Pump Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank suction jet pump can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, and put the driver's safety at risk.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the fuel tank inlet
fuel leaks from the passenger side rear wheel well
fuel gushing out of the tank
engine hesitancy
engine spluttering
engine stalling
strong smell of gasoline inside and outside the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EVAP canister can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, and put the driver's safety at risk.
symptoms: Fuel leaking from the charcoal canister
fuel leaking onto the ground by the passenger side rear wheel
strong smell of gasoline inside and outside the vehicle
dizziness while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A loose fuel line can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, and put the driver's safety at risk.
symptoms: Loud rattling noise from the right front (passenger) side
noise occurs at 2000-3500 engine RPM range
fuel line rattling against the chassis.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel line connection leak can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, and put the driver's safety at risk.
symptoms: Strong odor of gasoline noticeable to the driver and front-seat passenger
odor dissipates after starting the engine and running the ventilation fan
fuel line connection leak.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Activation of Forward Collision Assist/Automatic Emergency Braking System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of the Forward Collision Assist/Automatic Emergency Braking System can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop without warning, increasing the risk of rear-end collisions and accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops or brakes without warning
the system engages without an obstacle in front of the vehicle
the system activates at slow or moderate speeds
the system causes a sudden loss of control or unexpected braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A slow leak in the thermostat housing can cause coolant levels to drop, leading to engine overheating, damage, and potentially catastrophic failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Low coolant warning
coolant level drops below minimum levels
coolant leak noticed under the engine
coolant drips onto the driveway.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle's intermittent stalling can create a safety hazard, especially when it occurs in traffic, as it can be difficult to restart the vehicle and may cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls when coming to a stop in traffic while in gear
difficulty restarting the vehicle
check engine light may be illuminated
no codes stored by the computer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected shattering of the sunroof can cause a distraction to the driver, potentially leading to accidents, and may also result in injuries from broken glass.
symptoms: The sunroof shatters or crumbles without any apparent reason
starting from the front and center of the sunroof
and can expand over time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leaks from the panoramic roof can cause damage to the interior of the vehicle, including the headliner, upholstery, and electrical components, and may also lead to mold and mildew growth.
symptoms: Water leaks from the panoramic roof
causing wet spots on the headliner and pillars
fogging or condensation on the windshield
and staining of the upholstery.
